<?xml-stylesheet href="makehtml.xsl" type="text/xsl"?><section id="v113940507" revision="09212015222943" vendor="referenced"><title id="v113940605">Managing a device<token>PDM_device_details</token>
         </title><para id="v113940606">If an alert lets you know about issues with an individual device, you can check the device details for specific issues and take appropriate action. If a device status is <guilabel moreinfo="none">At Risk</guilabel> or <guilabel moreinfo="none">Compromised</guilabel>, for example, you would make sure that the device has the latest virus definitions. You can also check other settings, and perform basic remediation.</para><para id="v114289996">
            
         </para><para id="v113940649">
            See <a role="seelink" href="../TopicLink.action?ProdId=SCSEM&amp;vid=v107096381_v101064224" target="basefrm" title="Device status">Device status</a>
         </para><para id="v113940650">
            <xref xreflabel="Enrolling devices " linkend="v113799200" role="linkmoreinfo"/>
         </para><note id="v113940652"><para id="v113940682">Detailed device information is not available if a device status is <guilabel moreinfo="none">Pending</guilabel>.</para><para id="v113940653">Different details are available for different device platforms. For example, information about installed applications is not available for Windows devices.</para></note><table id="v113940607"><title>Table: Basic device management
